args:
One map led the party to a cave blocked
by a large boulder. After moving it aside,
they discover a dragon named Erasmus
who has secreted himself away inside.
This island is simply crawling with fiends!
With this many, the people of the island\nare bound to be attacked sooner or—
As if called from your very thoughts!
Please, you MUST do some scrying!
I expected to locate a fiend attack here,\nbut instead we find this poor woman\nsurrounded by some mad crowd!
Wait, Verica?! I thought you were coming\nhere to do some fortune-telling!
That was the plan, but I can't possibly\nhope to do so with this horde of people\ncrushing in on me!
Hold on! We're here to help!
Hooligans who spit in the face of\npublic decency are MY problem.
You lot there! Form a line, right now!\nThat's right, you too! One behind the other!
You really whipped 'em into shape...\nThat's the neatest line I've ever seen!
Well, this IS pretty much her specialty.
Heavens! Well, I think we know why\nher divination services are in such\nhigh demand at present.
In any case, I should be able to focus\non my scrying now, so thank you.
Happy to help. Just let us know\nif you need anything else.
Wait! Something is appearing in\nmy crystal ball...
Oh my! I saw a massive enemy standing\nbefore you, {player_name}!
I know not. However, I am certain that\nit will be all right regardless.
You hoisted something up—something that\nseemed set to repel the great beast.
That's good to know. Thank you.
I shall pray for your future success.
Thanks. Anyways, let's get moving—\nwe still need to find Ranzal and Celliera.
*pant* Enough! I can't do no more!\nYa beat me like an old carpet!
You would surrender so easily?\nNonsense! Keep going!
What brings you here in such a hurry?
We've learned some things about this\nisland. I'm glad to see you're all right.
And what, exactly, are you doing with\nthis massive boulder here?
We are attempting to move it!
Oh, riiiight. That makes sense.\n...Wait, no it doesn't!
It does if there's TREASURE behind it!
Accordin' to the map, our treasure is in\na cave right behind this here rock.
I'm afraid Ranzal and I could not\nso much as budge the boulder.
However, with you two lending sweat\nand tears to the cause, we will surely\nemerge victorious!
Is this really a question \nof winning or losing?
If I cannot even complete one simple task,\nhow can I possibly continue to call myself\na knight's armsmaster?!
That remains unchanged even during\na treasure hunt! If X marks a spot,\nI WILL arrive at said spot!
She's been like this all damn day.
The more traps she busted through,\nthe more it lit a fire under her.
Then there are traps here as well...\nI take it you also heard Siren?
You didn't hear a gorgeous voice singing?
Nope. Just Captain Muscles over here\nhummin' like she was havin' the time\nof her damn life.
If you have the energy for poor jokes,\nyou have the energy to move this rock!
Come, all of you! Put your backs into it!
Are you mad? It will take more than\nfour of us to move a stone this size!
Never claim something is impossible\nuntil you've tried it and failed!
To surrender without trying is pathetic,\nand I won't stand for it!
Guys, I think her eyes are literally\nturning into little flames here.
I don't think we're getting out of this,\nso we might as well start pushing.
Am I the ONLY one who finds this\nwhole endeavor ridiculous?!
It's maybe a tad aggressive, but I AM\ncurious if there's treasure back there.
Plus, Celliera is right: We can't just\ngive up without even trying first.
Now come, my little chickadees! Put your\nbacks into it and let's make this happen!
All right, all right, I'm coming. Sheesh!
Ain't like we really got a choice.\nReady? One...two...HEEEEEAVE!
You too, Notte! Get down here and put\nthose scrawny arms of yours to use!
You want MY help? Oh, this should be rich.\nBut hey, sure! I love pushin' stuff around!
Put your backs into it! Exceed your limits!\nMaximize the extreme! Embrace the pain!\nPUUUUUUUUSH!
I knew you could do it!
And now it is time to claim our\nrichly deserved treasure.
There's a dragon inside this cave!
How vexing to be mistaken\nfor THAT troublesome dragon.
Look out! I see blue flames!
I am the dragon Erasmus, and this flame\nis merely a guide for wandering sailors.\nSuch has always been my duty.

Siren, however, is ever bewitching sailors
and causing their ships to be dashed upon
the rocks—thereby undoing all of my
good works.
No matter how much I warn her from it,\nshe refuses to silence her song.
Then there are TWO dragons here?
That would be the proper math, yes.\nNow then, if I may, how did you figure\nout the trick to opening my cave?
If by trick ya mean throwin' out my\nachin' back, then yeah, we got it.
Then you did NOT use the secret button to \nroll the boulder aside? You actually forced\nit away using sheer physical strength?
THERE WAS A MAGIC MOVER SWITCH\nTHIS WHOLE TIME?!
You are skilled indeed to have fashioned\nsuch a clever device, dragon.
Ah, but I was not the switch's creator.\nThat credit goes to an adventurer\nby the name of Simon.
He lived with me for some time, but alas,\nhis moment in this world came to an end.
Such fleeting lives your kind have...
More of Barbary's stubborn minions?\nOh, but they hound me without end!
Less talkin', more choppin', boss!\nWe'll do the history lesson later!
